    1 │ /* should generate diagnostics */
  > 2 │ !foo === bar;
      │ ^^^^^^^^^^^^
    3 │ (!foo) === bar;
    4 │ (!foo) !== bar;
  
  i Due to operator precedence, the negation binds more tightly than the equality operator. The expression !foo === bar evaluates as (!foo) === bar, not !(foo === bar).
  
  i Replace !left operator right with the proper negated comparison, or wrap the comparison in parentheses with a negation.
  
  i This rule belongs to the nursery group, which means it is not yet stable and may change in the future. Visit https://biomejs.dev/linter/#nursery for more information.
  
  i Unsafe fix: Use the proper negated comparison operator instead.
  
